# Fake, disposable values for running tests against the Firestore/Auth
# Emulator (see `npm run test:emulator`). NONE of these are real -- the
# private key below is a throwaway RSA keypair generated solely for this
# file, never associated with any real Google Cloud project or service
# account, and is safe to commit for exactly that reason. The Firestore
# and Auth emulators do not validate credentials against Google's servers,
# so a syntactically-valid-but-fake key is all `cert()` needs to construct
# an Admin SDK app that talks only to the local emulator.
#
# This file is loaded only by the test runner (see vitest.setup.ts) and is
# never used by `next dev`/`next build`/`next start`, which rely on
# `.env.local` (never committed) instead.
